The use of annotations and descriptions from the web for feature extraction suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of filter banks, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research. The use of tags and keywords for feature extraction also suggests natural language processing (cs.CL) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of classification accuracy suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as another possible sub-category.
